<subSubSection id="DC92226FC2BC50B3E4424FDE9791C2EE" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph id="88204DA1F51FBFEEC60EB77909C1EEDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0210E9B1FCD821C676250B18478746A" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
Phylogenetic analyses indicated 
<taxonomicName id="F0EA84420FA59A2075BD33668888E3D9" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Dictyosporiaceae" genus="Dictyosporium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dictyosporium tratense" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="tratense">Dictyosporium tratense</taxonomicName>
nested within 
<taxonomicName id="D882B1924E010FC0A9457AB79149B7AD" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Dictyosporiaceae" genus="Dictyosporium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Dictyosporium" order="Pleosporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Dictyosporium</taxonomicName>
and close to 
<taxonomicName id="68C950231869A965BD699A2F47E83504" genus="D." lsidName="D. wuyiense" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="wuyiense">D. wuyiense</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from the other species in the genus in having a mucilaginous sheath. Morphologically, 
<taxonomicName id="01F8DDC4182364DA4BF4E45524A580D5" genus="D." lsidName="D. tratense" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="tratense">D. tratense</taxonomicName>
is most comparable to 
<taxonomicName id="4662D43D83FB6820B5E9C8FFF9488790" genus="D." lsidName="D. elegans" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="elegans">D. elegans</taxonomicName>
in conidial colour and shape, but conidia of the new taxon (40-57 
<normalizedToken id="DB7755FAA81BB30288CF08C7F24A5390" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
20-36 
<normalizedToken id="BBE1000C1F8D3682917FA68860DB8792" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) are smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName id="8BF3C6A0424B11B133EC20E3F717EE06" genus="D." lsidName="D. elegans" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="elegans">D. elegans</taxonomicName>
(40-80 
<normalizedToken id="A03CBE48B730CDD63FFFBB10D2F80C66" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
24-36 
<normalizedToken id="0C701042391CF34A7F228BC33E3126D7" originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="920B1F399C0F12BB4737645069BA7E1B" author="Goh, TK" journalOrPublisher="Fungal Diversity" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" pagination="65 - 100" title="A revision of the genus Dictyosporium, with descriptions of three new species." volume="2" year="1999">Goh et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
